# [SSHman](https://github.com/mwender/sshman) - Version {version}

# NAME
  sshman -- manage your SSH connections

# SYNOPSIS
  sshman [-vhs]

# DESCRIPTION
  SSHman requires that you have a .servers file setup in your $HOME directory. Format your .servers file like so (don't include the header row):

  server_name,ip,user(optional),port(optional),ssh_identity(optional)
  server.example.com,123.456.78.99,sysadmin,,~/.ssh/identity
  server2.example.com,223.14.56.89,"sysadmin,webdev,user3",2222

  The following options are available:

  -h, --help      displays this HELP file

  -s, --sftp      returns an SFTP connection string

  -v, --version   prints currently installed version